Introduction¶

Ford GoBike System Data: This data set includes information about individual rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area.

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The dataset contains of 183412 rows about trips and 16 features with a different types: (2 datetime --> start_time, end_time) (2 binary --> member_gender, bike_share_for_all_trip) (9 numeric --> duration_sec, start/end_station_id, start/end_station_latitude, start/end_station_longitude, bike_id,member_birth_year) (3 nominal --> start/end_station_name, user_type).

features describe the trip information (duration, start_time, end_time) features describe the location of the trip(start_station_id, start_station_name, start_station_latitude start_station_longitude end_station_id, end_station_name, end_station_latitude, end_station_longitude) features about user information (user_type, member_birth_year, member_gender)

I made some changes for the columns types

  • change the type of start_time, end_time from object to datetime.
  • change the type start_station_id, end_station_id, member_birth_year from float to integer.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I'm most interested on figuring out the duration of the trip.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

I think the duration of the trip mostly will affect with the location of the station start/end station, type of the user, age, and the gender.

Conclusions¶

The summary of the main findingsI notice during the data exploration:

  • The average of trip duration based on median is only 8.5 minutes. And the most from 14000 to 16000 trip duration between 5 to 10 minutes, also the longest trip duration is 23 hours.
  • For some reason 9 February registered the lowest number of trips.
  • The weekday registered number of trips 3X than weekend.
  • For the time at the morning 8 -9 am register the largest number of trips, and at evening 5-6 pm register the largest number of trips. While 1-4 am is the lowest number of trips at a day.
  • Station the station called “Market St at 10th St” is register the greatest number of the trip start the number of trips is exceeded 3900 trips while station called 16th ST Depot is register the lowest number of trips is registered only 34 trips.
  • The male users are more than female.
  • The subscriber users are more than customer users which is reasonable.
  • Most users ages between 20-40, is there ages used the bike till 100 (we might need more investigation for the older ages)
  • Although the subscriber users more than customers but the duration of the customer tip is more than the duration of subscriber users.
  • Both gender male and female duration trip almost same.
  • The subscriber user only shares the bike for all trip.
